Preheat #oven{} to 400 degrees.

> TIP: If you have a toaster oven, feel free to skip the preheating.

Wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Pick and finely chop fronds from @dill{1/4%ounce}.

Trim and grate @zucchini{1} on the largest holes of a #box grater{}. Place grated
zucchini in the center of a clean #kitchen towel{} or a couple layers of
#paper towels{} and toss with a big pinch of @salt{pinch}; set aside.

Thinly slice @roma tomato{1} into rounds.

== Creamy Dill Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{8%tablespoon}, lemon zest, half the
chopped dill, a squeeze of lemon juice, and up to 1/4 of the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}
to taste (you'll use the rest in the next step). Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

== Fritter Batter ==

Gather towel with grated zucchini into a tight bundle and wring over the
sink to remove excess moisture. Repeat process until zucchini is very dry.

In a #medium bowl{}, stir together @tempura mix{82%g}, half the
@feta cheese{1/4%cup} (you'll use the rest later), remaining chopped dill,
remaining garlic powder, 1/3 cup cold water, 1/2 tsp salt, and pepper until
smooth.

Stir in zucchini until evenly combined.

> TIP: Batter should be very thick but not dry; add a splash of water if
> necessary.

== Frying ==

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add tablespoon-sized scoops of batter.

> TIP: Work in batches if necessary, adding another drizzle of oil in between
> batches.

Cook until fritters are deeply golden and cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes} per
side.

> TIP: Lower heat if fritters begin to brown too quickly.

Transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Season with @salt{}.

== Toasting and Assembly ==

Meanwhile, toast @whole wheat pitas{2} in oven or toaster oven until warm and
pliable, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Halve pitas crosswise to create pockets; spread insides with as much creamy
dill sauce as you like. Fill with a few fritters, tomato, and as much
@arugula{2%ounce} as will fit.

Toss remaining arugula and remaining @feta cheese{1/4%cup} in a second
medium bowl with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, a squeeze of
lemon juice, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Divide pita pockets and salad between plates. Serve with any remaining creamy
dill sauce and fritters on the side.